@startuml
title ExcH-RAG-Agent - Kontext-Komponente

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
left to right direction

package "Kontext-Komponente" {
  class RuntimeEvent <<input>> {
    +payload: dict
  }

  class ContextInterpreter {
    +from_event(event: RuntimeEvent): RagIncidentContext
    +extract_snapshot(event: RuntimeEvent): RuntimeSnapshot
  }

  class RagIncidentContext <<dataclass>> {
    +correlationId: str
    +processName: str
    +summary: str
    +triggerEvent: str
    +lastSkill: str
    +xml_path: str
    +compact_event_context(): dict
    +runtime_context_note(): str
    +default_question(): str
  }

  class RuntimeSnapshot <<value object>> {
    +vars: List<ObservedValue>
    +rows: List<BrowseHint>
  }

  class ObservedValue <<value object>> {
    +id: str
    +type: str
    +value: Any
  }

  class BrowseHint <<value object>> {
    +id: str
    +node_class: str
    +type: str
  }

  ContextInterpreter ..> RuntimeEvent : liest
  ContextInterpreter --> RagIncidentContext : verdichtet zu
  ContextInterpreter --> RuntimeSnapshot : extrahiert
  RagIncidentContext o-- RuntimeSnapshot : nutzt
  RuntimeSnapshot *-- ObservedValue
  RuntimeSnapshot *-- BrowseHint
}

note right of RagIncidentContext
Kap. 3.4.2 betont:
- Trennung von Beobachtung und Strukturhinweis
- Verdichtung des Fehlerkontexts
- Aufbau eines Diagnosekontexts

Prototypischer Kern:
RagIncidentContext
end note

@enduml
